article.headline: Ohio 76, Central Michigan 44
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio (AP) -- Reserve Whitney Davis scored a career-high 17 points and Ohio held Central Michigan to just two field goals in the opening half in a 77-46 victory on Saturday. Central Michigan (2-11, 0-5 Mid-American Conference) trailed 35-7 at the half, hitting just 2-of-24 shots from the field. The Chippewas had as many shot-clock violations as they had field goals, and had 12 turnovers. Ohio (10-2, 4-0) scored the first seven points before Giordan Watson hit a 3-pointer at the 16-minute mark for the Chippewas. The Bobcats then ran off the next 24 points over a span of almost 13½ minutes -- Davis scoring 8, Williams 5 and Jeremy Fears 4 -- before Aaron Richie hit two free throws to break the drought for Central, which missed 15 consecutive shots from the field. Leon Williams and Jerome Tillman each scored 11 points and had 8 rebounds for the Bobcats. Tillman's scoring and rebounding totals were career highs. Watson had 14 points, Richie 11 and Sefton Barrett 10 for Central, which finished 13-of-56 from the field (23 percent).
